How to use class field declarations syntax in React classes?

```javascript
    class Counter extends Component {
      state = { value: 0 };

      handleIncrement = () => {
        this.setState((prevState) => ({
          value: prevState.value + 1,
        }));
      };

      handleDecrement = () => {
        this.setState((prevState) => ({
          value: prevState.value - 1,
        }));
      };

      render() {
        return (
            {this.state.value}

            <button onClick={this.handleIncrement}>+</button
